 anges thes  Date de on  crit _transaction  beim The answer must be a term that describes a situation when a person with mental illness can lead a relatively normal life. Managed is a term that describes a situation when a person with mental illness is able to control their symptoms. Effectively treated is a term that describes a situation when a person with mental illness receives enough treatment to control their symptoms. Recur means to happen again, which is not relevant to a person with mental illness leading a relatively normal life. Cause delusion is a term that describes a situation when a person with mental illness has symptoms that cause them to believe something that is not true. Illusion is a term that describes a situation when a person has a false belief that is not based on reality. So the answer is managed (a).

